      "content": "Don't just glob it on; you want a thick, consistent layer that completely covers the wound surface, like a medical poultice. Aim for about a teaspoon or two, enough so that the honey is visibly coating the entire cut and slightly oozing over the edges. This creates a moist healing environment, which is key, so make sure the dressing keeps it moist but covered.",
